<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039387FD5B745000FF17FE8F37545C5F:8EE560305B745000FF2FFEB636E65F7B" box="[172,214,309,330]" country="Georgia" municipality="LeConte's" name="This" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">This</location>
taxon was described from an unspecified number of specimens collected in « 
<collectingCountry box="[159,239,335,356]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Georgia</collectingCountry>
». 
<collectingMunicipality box="[261,360,335,356]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">LeConte’s</collectingMunicipality>
collection in 
<collectionCode box="[493,545,335,356]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" type="Museum">MCZ</collectionCode>
contains a single specimen under that name. The specimen, a female labelled «[orange disk]/Type 5698/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Lec." authorityName="Lec." box="[786,978,362,383]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piciventris">L. piciventris Lec.</taxonomicName>
[handwritten]» is herein designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[560,647,388,409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">lectotype</typeStatus>
and the label « 
<typeStatus box="[798,894,388,409]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Lectotype</typeStatus>
Argutor 
<taxonomicName authority="LeConte" authorityName="LeConte" box="[148,337,415,436]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piciventris">piciventris LeConte</taxonomicName>
des. 
<collectorName box="[390,511,415,436]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">Y. Bousquet</collectorName>
2004» has been added
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[148,978,309,622]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">
The 
<typeStatus box="[217,304,441,462]" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">lectotype</typeStatus>
(SBL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[370,388,442,462]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">¼</emphasis>
<quantity box="[395,471,441,462]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" unit="mm" value="5.2">5.2 mm</quantity>
) belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1828" box="[634,686,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agilis">
<emphasis box="[634,686,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">agilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and seems specifically different from all species treated by Allen (1972). It differs from members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chaudoir" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piceolus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. piceolus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1918" box="[240,369,495,516]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="accelerans">
<emphasis box="[240,369,495,516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. accelerans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[382,478,495,516]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="algidus">
<emphasis box="[382,478,495,516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. algidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1972" box="[533,641,495,516]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unilobus">
<emphasis box="[533,641,495,516]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. unilobus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of which the body sizes approach that of 
<taxonomicName box="[216,340,521,542]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piciventris">
<emphasis box="[216,340,521,542]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. piciventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in having the microsculpture well impressed on the frons, even at middle, the sides of pronotum less rounded, and other minute details. This taxon was considered a variety of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dejean)" baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[379,546,574,595]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis box="[379,456,574,595]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. velox</emphasis>
(Dejean)
</taxonomicName>
by Schaupp (1880:20). I have not seen any specimen of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dejean" baseAuthorityYear="1828" box="[273,350,601,622]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Loxandrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="150" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="velox">
<emphasis box="[273,350,601,622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="150">L. velox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
